referrals.intro: Take care of yourself! 😊 Your local clinic is here to help with any health problems. If you need extra support, here are some free helplines: ☎️
Seeing or going through violence can be scary and confusing. 😔 But there are people who can help you and your child! 💕
Feeling sad, stressed, or having trouble with your child's behaviour? 😟 These places can help: 💡

Family life can be tough! 😣 Did you know that social workers at your local Department of Social Development can help with parenting skills, fatherhood, teenage pregnancy, and family or relationship counselling? If there isn’t a DSD office near you, NGOs in your area offer this support too. 🌍
A lot of our energy goes into helping the person struggling with substance abuse. While that’s important, you and your family need support too! 💖 Find help for everyone below: ⬇️
Legal and SASSA issues can be stressful and confusing! 😵 There may be more support available than you realise at the organisations below: 👇
Understanding sexual and gender development can be confusing and hard to talk about. 🌈 We’re all unique! Here’s some support and guidance: 💡
